The Eyes of Tammy Faye is a 2000 documentary film about the life of Tammy Faye Bakker directed by Fenton Bailey and narrated by drag queen RuPaul.


== Reception ==
The film has a Rotten Tomatoes score of 86%, and is 23rd on the list of 50 Documentaries to See Before You Die on Current TV.


== Accolades ==
It won the Boston Society of Film Critics Award for Best Documentary Film and was nominated for Independent Spirit Award for Best Documentary Feature.


